# <%= projectName %>

Walking skeleton scaffolded by `@rgoussu.dev/keel`. Trunk-based,
hexagonal, Command/Query + Mediator, fakes-not-mocks, Quarkus REST,
Cloud Run (native image) via OpenTofu, GitHub Actions CD.

## Layout

```
application/rest/contract                     # OpenAPI spec + transport DTOs
application/rest/executable                   # Quarkus runnable (composition root)
domain/contract                               # ports + DTOs + mediator kernel
domain/contract/kernel                        # Action / Command / Query / Result / Error / Handler / Mediator
domain/core/<aggregate>                       # business logic (handlers)
infrastructure/<port>/{<impl>,fake}           # adapters + fake module
iac/cloudrun                                  # OpenTofu Cloud Run module
iac/bootstrap                                 # one-shot: enable APIs + create state bucket
.github/workflows                             # ci.yml (CD on main) + release.yml (manual promotion)
build-logic/                                  # gradle convention plugins
gradle/libs.versions.toml                     # version catalog
gradlew / gradle/wrapper/                     # Gradle Wrapper (shipped — no system gradle needed)
```

## First time: deploy to Cloud Run

```sh
# 1) Bootstrap the GCP side (enables APIs, creates the tofu state bucket).
PROJECT_ID=your-gcp-project REGION=europe-west1 ./iac/bootstrap/bootstrap.sh

# 2) Provision Artifact Registry, WIF pool/provider, deployer SA, and
#    runtime SA. (The Cloud Run service itself is created by CI on the
#    first push to main — do NOT `tofu apply` /iac/cloudrun by hand.)
cd iac/bootstrap
tofu init -backend-config=bucket=${PROJECT_ID}-tofu-state
tofu apply \
  -var project_id=${PROJECT_ID} \
  -var region=${REGION} \
  -var service_name=<%= projectName %> \
  -var github_repository=<owner>/<repo>

# 3) Copy the tofu outputs into GitHub Actions repo secrets:
#      GCP_PROJECT_ID            = ${PROJECT_ID}
#      GCP_REGION                = ${REGION}
#      GCP_WIF_PROVIDER          = $(tofu output -raw wif_provider)
#      GCP_DEPLOYER_SA_EMAIL     = $(tofu output -raw deployer_service_account_email)
#      GCP_RUNTIME_SA_EMAIL      = $(tofu output -raw runtime_service_account_email)
#      GCP_ARTIFACT_REGISTRY_URL = $(tofu output -raw artifact_registry_url)

# 4) Push to main. CI builds the native image, pushes, applies, smoke-
#    tests /ping. You should see a 200 JSON with {"message": "pong", ...}
#    at the service URL.
```

## Day-to-day

```sh
./gradlew check build              # local sanity
./gradlew :application:rest:executable:quarkusDev   # live-reload dev server on :8080
# /ping          → JSON ping response
# /openapi       → generated OpenAPI yaml
# /swagger       → Swagger UI
```

## Package group

Set the Java `group` on the root project by editing `build.gradle.kts`
and adding:

```kotlin
allprojects { group = "<%= basePackage %>" }
```

